# GitHub Repository Search Dropdown

A simple GitHub repository search bar with an autocomplete dropdown.  
Users can type a repository name and get live GitHub search results displayed in a dropdown menu.

## Features

- 🔍 Live GitHub repository search
- ⬇️ Autocomplete dropdown results
- ⌨️ Search input bar
- ⭐ Displays repository star count
- 🔗 Click results to open GitHub repositories
- ⏳ Debounced API requests to reduce calls
- 🖱️ Closes dropdown when clicking outside
- 🚀 Runs completely in the browser (no backend required)

---

# Input Bar

The search input allows users to enter a GitHub repository name.

Example:

```html
<input 
  id="search" 
  type="text"
  placeholder="Search GitHub repositories..."
/>
```

The input bar:

- Accepts user search queries
- Sends the text to the GitHub API
- Updates dropdown results automatically
- Shows matching repositories while typing

Example user input:

```
react
```

Dropdown output:

```
facebook/react
⭐ 230000+ stars

vuejs/core
⭐ 45000+ stars
```

